overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed functional specifications. The assistant conducted an
  in-depth analysis, identifying key areas where the implementation fell short
  of the acceptance criteria. Following this review, the assistant began
  implementing the identified gaps. The first two critical enhancements involved
  integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with
  dynamic safety warnings for high-risk scores, into the questionnaire's user
  interface and both web and PDF reports. Concurrently, the assistant developed
  and integrated logic for detecting and reporting Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea (COMISA), ensuring that this specific diagnosis is highlighted with
  appropriate recommendations in the generated reports. These changes involved
  updates to data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic.
